{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"04af1737-842f-4cd4-a92b-c03abfc86b86","content":"You already have the HotReload extension referenced. To use it, run your tests with `dotnet watch` in combination with `dotnet test`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test\n```\n\nThis will:\n1. **Run your tests** immediately\n2. **Watch for file changes** — every time you save a fix to `EmailValidatorTests.cs` (or any source file), it automatically re-runs the tests using hot reload\n3. **Give fast feedback** — hot reload patches your code in-place without a full rebuild\n\nJust edit your test/source files, save, and see results instantly in the terminal. Press `Ctrl+C` to stop.\n\n> **Tip:** The `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package enables the testing platform's hot-reload support so that `dotnet watch test` can re-execute tests without restarting the test host each time.\n\nWant me to start it up and help you fix the failing tests?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3a2a2702-4e4c-476f-a54e-1efec02c051e","outputTokens":216},"id":"22ea2610-438c-4e2b-a1ca-08817e50fd19","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:41:46.869Z","parentId":"520a540b-7223-470e-974a-850562c5b95e"}
